<FIRST>r a PM-People-Oprah     05-22 0333</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-People-Oprah,0343</SECOND>
<HEAD>Oprah Winfrey Gives $1 Million To College</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Talk show host Oprah Winfrey received an honorary
doctorate from Morehouse College and gave $1 million to establish a
scholarship at the private men's college.
   ``The world awaits what you have to give,'' she said after
receiving an honorary Doctor of Humane Letters degree during
commencement ceremonies Sunday. ``The pressure is on.''
   Ms. Winfrey said she established the Oprah Winfrey Endowment
Scholarship Fund because she felt she should share her good
fortune. She chose Morehouse because the students and faculty
treated her warmly during a January 1988 visit, including sending
her a sweatshirt, she said.
   ``I wear that sweatshirt like I know everybody at Morehouse,''
she said. ``Now that I have this doctorate, people are going to
have to get a special dispensation to talk to me.''
   The college is distinguished by at least one famous graduate,
Martin Luther King Jr.
   King's son, Dexter, also attended the school, which is the site
the Martin Luther King Jr. International Chapel.
   Earlier Sunday, Ms. Winfrey told the congregation at West Hunter
Street Baptist Church, near downtown Atlanta, that she tries to
keep a positive attitude because to do otherwise ``damages your
spirit.''
   Ms. Winfrey recounted stories from her youth while speaking to
an overflow crowd, calling her life ``a long journey from just a
little colored girl to an African-American woman.''
   ``I, like a lot of people here, spent a lot of time trying to be
somebody I was not,'' she said. ``I spent a lot of time trying to
be Diana Ross ... then trying just to be someone supreme and to
stop somebody in the name of love.''
   She said that because of her celebrity status, she is exposed to
vicious rumors, which she tries to ignore.
   ``Every single negative thing you do damages your spirit,'' she
said. ``It keeps you from flying. The reason so many people can't
fly is because they've got too much garbage in their wings.''
</TEXT>
