<HEAD>Storms in Nation's Heartland</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   The nation's heartland was hit by a rash of thunderstorms today
as a band of East Coast storms lost its punch.
   Thunderstorms were clustered in northern Oklahoma, central and
eastern Kansas and southern and central Missouri. Other bands of
thunderstorms were moving out of eastern Arkansas into western
Tennessee and northern Mississippi.
   Showers and thunderstorms developing ahead of an upper level
weather system were scattered across eastern South Dakota and
southeastern North Dakota.
   Thunderstorms that developed ahead of a cold front in the East
produced severe weather in North Carolina Sunday evening and then
weakened as they moved out to sea.
   Showers developing ahead of the same cold front fell in eastern
Maine and off the coast of Massachusetts this morning.
   Dry weather prevailed across the rest of the nation.
   Today's forecast called for showers and thunderstorms across
much of the Mississippi, Ohio and Tennessee valleys and Gulf Coast
states to Florida; scattered showers in northeastern New York state
and northern New England; and rain spreading into the Pacific
Northwest.
   Predicted highs: 60s along the northern California coast and
from the Pacific Northwest to northwest Montana; near 90 in
Florida, Mississippi and Louisiana; 90s in the southern Plains; 95
to 105 in southwest Texas and the desert Southwest; and 70s to 80s
across most of the rest of the nation.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 35
degrees at Yellowstone Park, Wyo., to 84 at Phoenix.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 68 fair; Boston 59 fair; Buffalo 50 fair;
Charleston, S.C., 72 partly cloudy; Cincinnati 65 cloudy; Cleveland
54 cloudy; Detroit 55 fair; Miami 74 fair; New York 60 foggy;
Philadelphia 61 fair; Pittsburgh 57 partly cloudy; Portland, Maine
51 fair; Washington 61 partly cloudy.
   _Central: Bismarck 47 fair; Chicago 62 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth
77 windy; Denver 53 fair; Des Moines 56 cloudy; Indianapolis 65
cloudy; Minneapolis-St. Paul 64 cloudy; Nashville 67 cloudy; New
Orleans 72 foggy; St. Louis 67 cloudy.
   _West: Albuquerque 71 fair; Anchorage 40 fair; Las Vegas 78
windy; Los Angeles 57 fair; Phoenix 82 partly cloudy; Salt Lake
City 57 fair; San Diego 61 fair; San Francisco 51 fair; Seattle 51
partly cloudy.
   _Canada: Montreal 55 rain; Toronto 50 fair.
