<DATELINE>COLOMBO, Sri Lanka (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two rival Tamil rebel groups battled
in a northern jungle, and at least 51 people were killed, the
military said today.
   Guerrillas of the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam, the largest
Tamil rebel organization, attacked a camp of the People's
Liberation Organization of Tamil Eelam in Mannar district, 140
miles north of Colombo, said the military officials, who cannot be
