for an independent Tamil nation. But recently they accepted a
government offer for talks, and five rebel leaders are negotiating
with officials in Colombo.
   Tamil guerrillas began their separatist war in 1983, claiming
they were discriminated against by the island nation's majority
Sinhalese.
