<HEAD>30 Dead, 128 Missing in Ship Accident Off Bali</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: One name only is cq for Wardojo.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JAKARTA, Indonesia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A passenger ship sank off the tourist
island of Bali, killing at least 30 people and leaving 128 others
missing and feared dead, an official said Monday.
   The missing were believed to be trapped in the ship, the Dharma
Mulia, which capsized Sunday when it was struck by huge waves,
according to Wardojo, a Search and Rescue Agency official.
   ``Hopes are very slim that any of them are still alive,'' he
said.
   The ship was carrying 325 people, mostly workers on their way
from Lombok to Malaysia, he said. It went down off the town of
Benoa in southern Bali.
   Rescue workers recovered four bodies and brought 167 passengers
to safety Sunday night.
   Wardojo said by telephone from Bali's capital of Denpasar that
rescuers recovered another 26 bodies Monday.
   Bali is about 750 miles southeast of Jakarta.
