<HEAD>Three Dead in Cargo Plane Crash</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: UPDATES with dead all crew members, destination and cargo unknown.
No pickup.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DE KALB, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A DC-3 cargo plane crashed and burned in a
rural area near here today, killing all three crew members,
authorities said.
   The twin-propeller plane went down around 10:45 a.m. after
takeoff from an airport near Aurora, about 25 miles from here, said
Lee Carlson, a Federal Aviation Administration spokesman.
   Killed were three employees of Condor Enterprise Inc., which
owned the plane, said Ernie Kobrow, vice president of the company
based at Aurora Municipal Airport.
   Carlson said he did not know the plane's destination.
   It was not immediately known if the plane was carrying any
cargo, said Barbara Dettmer, an FAA spokeswoman.
   Investigators from the National Transportation Safety Board were
sent to the scene.
   De Kalb is about 60 miles west of Chicago.
