<FILEID>AP-NR-05-22-89 2251EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>d a AM-BRF--BungledBurglary     05-22 0121</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Bungled Burglary,0122</SECOND>
<HEAD>Police: Man Just Released From Jail Tries Burglary for Money to Get
Home</HEAD>
<DATELINE>EUGENE, Ore. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man released from jail after he was
charged with burglary was arrested again less than two hours later
when police answered a burglar alarm at a tire store.
   Police said they identified Kirk Stanley Manning, 19, by the
release papers in his pocket.
   Manning was released on his own recognizance Friday night, three
days after his arrest in Florence on burglary and theft charges.
Manning told officiers he entered the business to get enough money
to return to Florence, about 55 miles west of Eugene, police said.
He was charged with burglary and jailed, this time on $1,000 bail.
