<HEAD>Officer Bitten Making Domestic Disturbance Arrest</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HOLLANDALE, Miss. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A police officer was hospitalized in
stable condition Monday after his bottom lip and part of his chin
were bitten off when he was making an arrest during a domestic
dispute.
   Police Chief Jerry Redmond said Monday that the incident
occurred when Sgt. Jester Johnson, 43, responded to a disturbance
call outside a nightclub early Sunday.
   Redmond said Johnson arrested Isaiah Wright, 26, of Hollandale,
who allegedly was fighting with a woman.
   The police chief said that as Johnson was trying to handcuff
Wright, the suspect bite the officer in the face and threw him to
the ground. Another officer apprehended Wright.
   Wright is in the Hollandale City Jail and was to be tested for
the AIDS virus, Redmond said. He is held pending arraignment on
charges of aggravated assault on a police officer and resisting
arrest.
   Johnson is in a Memphis, Tenn., hosptial where he is expected to
undergo plastic surgery.
