<FIRST>r a AM-TransplantBaby     05-22 0206</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Transplant Baby,0212</SECOND>
<HEAD>Youngest Multitransplant Baby Has Third Birthday</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The youngest person ever to undergo four liver
transplants has celebrated her third birthday playing with a new
Barbie doll and swing set.
   ``There was a time when I didn't think we'd see her first
birthday, let alone her third,'' said Shirley LaRocco said of her
daughter, Meghann.
   ``But our prayers were answered, and now she's doing just
fine,'' she said. ``We're just so excited she's doing so well. This
is the first year she's known it's her birthday.''
   She said Meghann played with her gifts for most of the day
Sunday.
   Meghann was born with biliary atresia, a a fatal liver defect,
and complications necessitated the series of transplants in
November and December 1986.
   Chicagoans rushed donations to the family to help defray medical
costs. Officials of the University of Chicago Hospitals had
estimated the cost of Meghann's treatment at $500,000.
   Doctors estimate Meghann's chances for a full recovery at 80
percent to 85 percent. She no longer has to make regular visits to
the doctor but continues to take an anti-rejection drug,
cyclosporine, every day.
   ``She's just like any normal child now,'' said her father,
Frank. ``She's even taking roller-skating lessons.''
