<HEAD>Fishermen Blown to Shore After 18-Hour Ordeal In Lake</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OSHKOSH, Wis. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two fishermen who clung to their overturned
boat for 18 hours were finally blown ashore by a friendly wind.
   ``We sang every song we knew and we sang them again to keep
awake and mentally sharp,'' said Larry Olson, 45, of his overnight
stay in Lake Winnebago.
   He and his brother-in-law Bruce Schiedermayer, 31, were blown
ashore Sunday morning after their boat took on water as they were
fishing Saturday about 2{ miles from Oshkosh.
   They said their bilge pump wasn't working properly and couldn't
pump out the water which finally dampened batteries causing them to
lose all power.
</TEXT>
