<HEAD>Ouachita Parish Eligible for Disaster Relief</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush declared on Monday that a
``major disaster'' exists in Louisiana because of severe storms and
flooding, and he directed federal aid to help recovery efforts in
the stricken areas.
   The action makes federal funds and low-cost loans available to
residents of Ouachita Parish affected by the storms, which began on
May 5.
   The White House statement said the Federal Emergency Management
Agency might make other parishes eligible for help after damage
surveys are completed.
   Robert D. Broussard, director of FEMA's regional office in
Texas, was named to coordinate federal recovery operations in the
area.
   Assistance can include temporary housing, loans, grants, and
other programs to help individuals and business owners.
