<FIRST>r a AM-WritersHonored 2ndLd-Writethru a0681 05-22 0312</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Writers Honored, 2nd Ld - Writethru, a0681,0318</SECOND>
<HEAD>New Jersey Writer Takes Columnist Award</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: ADDS 7 grafs with other winners, prizes.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MYSTIC, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rosemary Parrillo of the Courier-Post in
Camden, N.J., won first place in the General Interest division,
circulation over 65,000, of a competition sponsored by the National
Society of Newspaper Columnists.
   Fred Flaxeman, a self-syndicated columnist from Glenview, Ill.,
won the General Interest division in the under-65,000 circulation
category in the awards announced Friday.
   The writing competition attracted 285 entries. Winners each
received $200 and a plaque.
   Colin McEnroe of The Hartford (Conn.) Courant, took first place
in Humor, circulation over 65,000, and John Young of Waco, Texas,
captured the under-65,000 category for his column in the Waco
Tribune-Herald.
   Doug Robarchek of The Charlotte (N.C.) Observer won the Items
category, which had no circulation cutoff.
   The organization, holding its convention here, is based in
Louisville, Ky., and comprises approximately 200 general interest
columnists, both staff writers and syndicated.
   Other winners were:
   General Interest, over 65,000: Second place, Richard Prince, The
Rochester Democrat and Chronicle and the Times-Union, Rochester,
N.Y.; third place, Joe Soucheray, The St. Paul Pioneer Press
Dispatch, St. Paul, Minn.
   General Interest, under 65,000: Second place, Jim Kreshner, the
Valley Daily News, Kent, Wash.; third place, tie, Jim Files, The
Apache Junction Independent, Apache Junction, Ariz., and Dolores
Laschever, the Register Citizen, Torrington, Conn.
   Humor, over 65,000: Second place, Doug Clark, the
Spokesman-Review, Spokane, Wash.; third place, Terry Marotta, a
self-syndicated columnist writing out of Winchester, Mass.
   Humor, under 65,000: Second place, Christopher Cox, The Sun,
Lowell, Mass.; third place, Andrew Heller, the Saginaw News,
Saginaw, Mich.
   Items: Second place, Bob Toren, the Georgetown Gazette,
Georgetown, Calif.; third place, Martin Snapp, The Tribune,
Oakland, Calif.
   First-place winners received $200 and a plaque; second place,
$100 and a plaque; third place, $50 and a plaque.
</TEXT>
