<HEAD>From AP Newsfeatures</HEAD>
<HEAD>With BC-APN--Johns Hopkins</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   
   BALTIMORE (AP) _ What does it take to keep the 1,077-bed Johns
Hopkins Hospital running? Here are some approximate annual figures:
   _7.2 million rubber gloves.
   _3.7 million needles and syringes.
   _More than 6,000 gallons of floor wax.
   _4.8 million pounds of clean wash.
   _More than 3 million meals.
   _The cafeteria alone sells 8 miles of Hoagie sandwiches, 50,000
pieces of chicken and 280,000 slices of pizza. And customers wipe
up the mess with nearly 9.4 million napkins.
</TEXT>
