<FIRST>r f BC-CompaqComputer     05-22 0185</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Compaq Computer,0195</SECOND>
<HEAD>Compaq Unveils New Personal Computer Billed As Most Powerful</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HOUSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Compaq Computer Corp. today unveiled its new
desktop personal computer, which the company billed as the world's
most powerful and expandable.
   The three 33-megahertz COMPAQ DESKPRO 386@33 models are designed
for applications including computer-aided design, financial
modeling and software development.
   They also can be used as ``fie servers'' or common information
centers for offices that use other less powerful machines at
individual work stations.
   Compaq said the new computer model features a streamlined
ergonomic system unit design that provides eight expansion slots
and room for five storage devices for a maximum of 1.3 gigabytes of
internal memory storage, which the Houston-based company said
exceeds that of any other desktop personal computer now available.
   It uses the COMPAQ Flex Architecture that combines Intel's most
advanced 386 processor, the new 33-megahertz Intel 386.
   The new Compaq series of three models range in price from nearly
$10,500 to almost $18,000. Worldwide shipments will begin this
month, with deliveries in June.
   Compaq is a major manufacturer of desktop, portable and laptop
personal computers.
</TEXT>
