<FIRST>r f BC-ReynoldsTobaccoChairman     05-22 0313</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Reynolds Tobacco Chairman,0321</SECOND>
<HEAD>Citibank Executive Named CEO of R.J. Reynolds Tobacco</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   WINSTON-SALEM, N.C. (AP) _ James W. Johnston of Citibank has
been appointed chairman and chief executive officer of R.J.
Reynolds Tobacco USA effective June 1, company officials announced
Monday.
   Johnston, 43, division executive with the Northeast Division of
Citibank, will report to Louis Gerstner, Jr., chairman and chief
executive officer of RJR Nabisco Inc., the Atlanta-based parent
company of R.J. Reynolds Tobacco USA.
   Before joining Citibank in 1984, Johnston was executive vice
president for U.S. sales, marketing and product development for
R.J. Reynolds Tobacco Co. for three years. From 1979 until 1981, he
was president and chief executive officer for the Asia-Pacific
region of R.J. Reynolds Tobacco International Inc.
   ``The selection of Jim Johnston to head R.J. Reynolds Tobacco
USA marks the return of a highly experienced tobacco executive to
our company and to Winston-Salem,'' Gerstner said in a prepared
statement.
   ``In both our international and domestic tobacco businesses, Jim
proved himself to be a builder of brands, an outstanding sales
executive and a skilled manager of people,'' Gerstner said.
``Reynolds Tobacco USA already has outstanding brands and talented,
committed employees, and Jim will be a real asset in providing
direction and leadership for the 1990s.''
   Johnson, a native of Illinois, succeeds Chief Executive Officer
Ralph Angiuoli, who is retiring June 1.
   ``My top priorities will be to work with members of management
and the employees of Reynolds Tobacco USA to produce the best
quality products, build brand strength, and sharpen the focus on
customers, as well as to increase profitability and create an
effective organization to ensure our company's success in the years
ahead,'' Johnston said.
   RJR Nabisco is an international consumer products company. RJR
Nabisco's major operating companies are R.J. Reynolds Tobacco USA,
R.J. Reynolds Tobacco International Inc., Nabisco Brands Inc., Del
Monte Foods and Planters LifeSavers Co.
</TEXT>
