<FIRST>u f AM-EntrepreneurialWoman     05-22 0269</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Entrepreneurial Woman,0279</SECOND>
<HEAD>Entrepreneur Magazine Publishers Plans Biz Magazine for Women</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The publishers of Entrepreneur Magazine said
Monday they intend to begin publishing a magazine designed for
women who are starting their own businesses.
   The magazine will be called Entrepreneurial Woman which will
debut with an issue in June and appear once every two months
starting in February.
   ``This is a business magazine for women,'' said Clare Thain,
publisher and president of the Irvine, Calif.-based magazine
concern. ``There is a great distinction between this magazine and
publications like Working Woman and Savvy, which are lifestyle
magazines for women who work.''
   The magazine will provide practical advice on how to start a
business and keep it running, much as the magazine Entrepreneur has
provided.
   But Thain said Entrepreneurial Woman will consistently address
issues of relevance to women, such as how to obtain financing and
how to balance business with family responsibilities as well as
stories on women role models.
   The first issue, for instance, has stories on cars suited to
women's entreprenuerial lifestyles, the prospects for the
infant-products industry and the only woman to run a record label.
   Thain said he is convinced there is a market for such a magazine
because one in four subscribers to Entrepreneur are women and
government statistics indicate four out of five new business owners
are women.
   He said his two magazines will not carry the same stories and as
a result should not dilute the original magazine's circulation.
   Entrepreneur has a circulation rate base of 300,000 effective in
July. Entrepreneurial Woman will have a rate base of 200,000.
</TEXT>
