<HEAD>Fruehauf Loses $241.7 Million in First Quarter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Fruehauf Corp. reported Monday $241.7 million in
first- quarter losses, mostly in estimated losses from the sales of
its trailer and marine divisions.
   Freuhauf, the trucking and automitive parts maker that was sold
to Varity Corp. earlier this month, said the one-time loss for the
two divisions was $236 million.
   Without the loss from the sales, the company reported losses of
$5.7 million in the first three months of the year, compared with
$16.4 million in losses in the same 1988 period.
   Sales during the quarter rose to $332.9 million from $257.8
million in the first three months of last year.
   Fruehauf in March said a subsidiary of Terex Corp. had bought
the company's trailer and maritime operations for about $232.5
million. The rest of Fruehauf was sold to Varity for $436 million
and 55.5 million shares of Varity stock.
</TEXT>
